The paper deals with image manipulation and detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep convolutional neural networks suggests that it may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM). The paper specifically addresses splicing detection, which is a subfield of image forensics and security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning also suggests that it may fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
